# swiggy-assignment# üõçÔ∏è AI Shopping Assistant (LangGraph + GPT-4 Vision + Claude)

A multi-turn conversational AI agent that understands your product preferences from images üñºÔ∏è or user chat üß† and recommends items from a local catalog ‚Äî all powered by **LangGraph**, **GPT-4 Vision**, and **Claude 3.7 Sonnet**.

> Built with ‚ù§Ô∏è for smart, adaptive, and delightful shopping experiences.

---

## ‚ú® Features

### üì∏ Image-Driven Intelligence
- Upload any **product image** (e.g., a sneaker or gadget).
- GPT-4 Vision analyzes the image and **infers the product type** automatically.
- No need for manual tagging or labeling!

### üí¨ Adaptive Clarification (LLM-Powered)
- The agent **asks tailored follow-up questions** depending on product category.
  - E.g., "What size?" for sneakers or "What features?" for electronics.
- Choose from:
  - **GPT-4** (via OpenAI)
  - **Claude 3.5 Sonnet** (via Anthropic)
  - **Mock mode** (for offline/local testing)

### üß† Smart Recommendation Engine
- Matches against a curated `mock_products.json` database.
- Flexible filters:
  - üéØ Brand
  - üé® Color
  - üí∏ Price range
  - üì¶ Category
  - üß© Feature preferences
- Works even when preferences are vague or missing ‚Äî thanks to fuzzy matching.

### üìÇ Robust CLI Interaction
- Choose to:
  - Upload your own image,
  - Use a **default image (`nike-sneaker.jpg`)**, or
  - Paste an **image URL** (auto-downloads and converts to base64).

Since I currently don't have access to an OpenAI or Anthropic API key (credit card required), I‚Äôve painstakingly memorized and replicated their message formats to implement a fully functional Mock Mode üé≠.

This ensures the agent works offline and is API-key ready ‚Äî just plug in your keys when available üîë.

üß† The logic, flow, and architecture mirror production-ready setups, making this ideal for future extension with real API access.


### ‚öôÔ∏è Extensible Graph Architecture (via LangGraph)
- Modular agent nodes:
  - `image_analyzer`
  - `user_clarifier`
  - `product_recommender`
- Easy to extend with new nodes (e.g., vector search, real-time price lookup).
